The late actor Dumisani Masilela’s legacy lives on! It’s been four years since the Scandal actor passed away in hospital after he was shot during a hijack incident in Tembisa. Thanks to Ekurhuleni Mayor Mzwandile Masina, who kept his promise he made at Dumi’s funeral, the Germiston theatre will now be named after the former idols runner up. According to Masina the name change will take place at the theatre on Tuesday next week. Masina revealed the details on his social media account that Germiston theatre will now be called Dumisani Masilele theatre.